# Whitelist .dockerignore (CLAUDE.md §4: the repo is PUBLIC — the build context
# must never carry data blobs, secrets, .git, or the local-only working docs).
# The CI image (docker/Dockerfile) needs ONLY the two committed conda-lock files.
# Exclude everything, then re-include just those, so the build context stays tiny.
*
!envs
envs/*
!envs/ml-dna.conda-lock.yml
!envs/ml-rna.conda-lock.yml
